parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Driver Seat Failure Due to Bolt Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the driver seat bolts can cause the seat to collapse or recline backwards, leading to loss of control, accidents, or injuries.
symptoms: The driver seat collapses or reclines backwards
the seat bolts fail or shear off
the seat becomes unstable or wobbly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent speedometer and brake issues can cause loss of power brakes, leading to extended stopping distances, and potentially causing accidents.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Rear Brake Lockup and ABS Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rear brake lockup and ABS failure can cause the vehicle to jump forward, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Fade and Extended Stopping Distance
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The brake fade and extended stopping distance can cause accidents, especially at high speeds.
The front brake failure and wear can cause extended stopping distances, leading to potential accidents.
The ABS system malfunction can cause loss of control, leading to accidents, especially during emergency stops.

Tread separation can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents, injuries, and fatalities. In this case, a police officer became a paraplegic after a vehicle rollover accident caused by tread separation.
